Subject: [PATCH] riscv64 Rust-core bun: include <wtf/Scope.h> in JSModuleLoader.cpp

Building oven-sh/WebKit @ 963f8758 (the WEBKIT_VERSION pinned by the Rust-core
bun target_commit, distinct from the Zig-era 5488984d) as JSCOnly+C_LOOP for
riscv64: JSModuleLoader.cpp uses WTF::makeScopeExit (runtime/JSModuleLoader.cpp
~line 1176) but does not include <wtf/Scope.h> directly, and it is not pulled in
transitively in the JSCOnly configuration. Add the include.

This is an upstream-safe, additive include; not riscv64- or C_LOOP-specific.

Rebased against 963f8758 (Rust-core WebKit). The three other hunks the
5488984d-era 0007 carried are now OBSOLETE upstream and were dropped:
  - heap/Heap.cpp already includes <wtf/SetForScope.h> (line 110).
  - runtime/DeferredWorkTimer.cpp already includes <wtf/SetForScope.h> (line 36).
  - bytecode/ArithProfile.h now uses the *unqualified* `friend class
    LLIntOffsetsExtractor;` (not the qualified `JSC::` form), which itself
    introduces JSC::LLIntOffsetsExtractor into the namespace, so the separate
    forward declaration is no longer required.

diff --git a/Source/JavaScriptCore/runtime/JSModuleLoader.cpp b/Source/JavaScriptCore/runtime/JSModuleLoader.cpp
index 46bf6f4ddf..80bb07d7d6 100644
--- a/Source/JavaScriptCore/runtime/JSModuleLoader.cpp
+++ b/Source/JavaScriptCore/runtime/JSModuleLoader.cpp
@@ -50,6 +50,7 @@
 #include "SyntheticModuleRecord.h"
 #include "TopExceptionScope.h"
 #include "VMTrapsInlines.h"
+#include <wtf/Scope.h>
 #include <wtf/text/MakeString.h>

 namespace JSC {
